 <fr:p>The inverse to the <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">identity function</fr:link> <fr:tex>\mathsf {id}_{ A } \colon  A \to  A</fr:tex> is simply itself.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Fix <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">bijections</fr:link> <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>g \colon  B \to  C</fr:tex>, so that we have <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">inverses</fr:link> <fr:tex>f ^{-1} \colon  B \to  A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>g ^{-1} \colon  C \to  B</fr:tex>. The <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">inverse</fr:link> to the <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">composite function</fr:link> <fr:tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</fr:tex> is the <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
